@node "introduction" "introduction"
 INTRODUCTION

I make this utility for the use of ,I think, the most popular genlock on the
Amiga market, the G-LOCK by GVP.

With GLC you can control by the keyboard, some of G-LOCK functions like color
control,hue,brightness,saturation,video source and  even load an IFF file for
overlay graphics, with some "IN" and "OUT" effects, with any size.

This utility make use of the amazing Cando, Arexx and G-Lock posibilities.







G-LOCK (R) is copyright 1992 Great Valley Products,Inc.  CanDO is copyright
Inovatronics. ARexx is copyright William Hawes.
@endnode

@node "installation" "installation"


To install copy the program onto your desired drawer,and copy the
candogfx.library on your system LIBS: directory.

To work properly this program only run if you have RexxMast running and GL or
SGL,both programs provided with your G-LOCK running previously.
@endnode

@node "usage" "usage"


 USAGE:
  

 This program convert your AMIGA keyboard on a "controller" of the G-LOCK.
 First you must run ARexx on your system and GL or SGL programs for GLock.
 Once you start GLC, you can control some G-Lock functions by pressing
 appropiates keys on the Amiga keyboard.


 -------------------->>>>All keys on GLC are NO CAPS !!!<<<<----------------


 By pressing "HELP" you can see all keys commands.

 By pressing "f" you go to the IFF settings,and In and Out effects.

 By pressing "m" you go to main panel.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

 QUICK OVERVIEW (ABOUT IFF IMAGES)

 1) Once you start GLC program,press "f", to go to IFF SETTINGS .
 2) Then press "z" to load an IFF file,select the file.(The file must be
    an IFF)
 3) Set the width and height of IFF file by the sliders on screen.
 4) Press "c" to see the IFF file,and "v" to clear IFF.
 5) To change the position of IFF file, put the pointer on any place 
    on screen and press "a".
 6) Then select the IN-OUT effect on effects list,by click on the
    desired effect, and press the UP or DOWN arrows to change the
    speed of IN-OUT effect.
 7)With the settings right for you, press "m" to go to main panel.

 8)Then by pressing "c" you see the IFF file and with "v" you clear screen.
 
 9)If you want other IFF you must press "x" and then "z" to load other.

 10)I hope you understand my VERY POOR ENGLISH..

 The program have presetted IN and OUT effects on 0 to 9 keypad, to let you
 change the IN and OUT effect without go to IFF Settings panel.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------


                              
                        KEYBOARDS COMMANDS
                         G-LOCK SETTINGS  

                  
         
  By pressing  "1" key or "q" you can set the BRIGHTNESS 
               
               "2"        "w" you can set the CONTRAST
               
               "3"        "e" you can set the HUE
               
               "4"        "r" you can set the SATURATION
               
               "5"        "t" you can set the BLUE GAIN
               
               "6"        "y" you can set the BLUE DC
               
               "7"        "u" you can set the RED GAIN
               
               "8"        "i" you can set the RED DC
               
               "9" you can set RED COMPONENT OUT
               
               "0" you can set GREEN COMPONENT OUT
               
               "-" you can set BLUE COMPONENT OUT
 
              "TAB" key set the G-Lock to Factory values

              "LEFT-RIGHT" arrows set Video Source 1 or 2

              "DEL" delete the pointer.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------








  
    IFF COMMANDS 

              
   By pressing "z" key you can LOAD IFF file.

               "x" key you can DELETE IFF file.

               "a" key you can set POSITION OF IFF file on screen.

               "c" key you can PUT THE IFF file on screen.

               "v" key you can OUT THE IFF file of screen.

               "0 to 9" keys on KEYPAD, you can change some In and OUT
                        effects.(Presetted by program)

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
